        Bot["chatbot.py — SalesChatbot (Orchestrator)
chat() 8-step order per turn:
  1 get_current_prompt  2 analyze_state+record_intent  3 provider.chat (LLM)
  4 fallback: sambanova → openrouter → static msg  5 add_turn+save_session
  6 log_stage_latency  7 _apply_advancement  8 classify_objection (OBJECTION only)
_detect_and_switch_strategy() — INTENT mode only, post-LLM
_apply_advancement() — triggers FSM stage or strategy transition
rewind(n) · rewind_to_turn(i) · replay(history) · save_session() · load_session()"]
        FSM["flow.py — SalesFlowEngine
3 strategies: INTENT (discovery) · CONSULTATIVE (5-stage NEPQ) · TRANSACTIONAL (3-stage)
strategy_for_prompts: INTENT mode → CONSULTATIVE templates
get_advance_target() — 5 ordered evaluation paths:
  1 commitment signal at LOGICAL/EMOTIONAL → PITCH (fast-path)
  2 user_demands_directness() → PITCH
  3 direct_info_requests keywords → PITCH
  4 urgency_skip_to + impatience → skip stage
  5 ADVANCEMENT_RULES[advance_on](history, msg, stage_turn_count)
ADVANCEMENT_RULES dict: user_has_clear_intent · user_shows_doubt
  user_expressed_stakes · commitment_or_objection · commitment_or_walkaway"]
        NLU["analysis.py — Pure NLU (zero LLM calls)
analyze_state(history, user_message) → ConversationState {intent · guarded · fatigue · decisive}
classify_intent_level(): intent lock — once 'high', never regresses
detect_guardedness(): 4 priority cases + weighted scoring (evasive×0.5 · sarcasm×0.35
  deflection×0.2 · defensive×0.1) + context multiplier ×1.4 if short reply to long bot msg
classify_objection(): 7 types from signals.yaml (first keyword match wins)
text_contains_any_keyword(): @lru_cache compiled regex · negation-aware finditer loop"]
        Content["content.py · prompts.py · overrides.py · tactics.py
4-tier prompt assembly on every turn:
  Tier 1 override (early-exit — skips 2–4):
    direct_info_request · soft_positive at PITCH · repetitive_validation loop
  Tier 2 acknowledgment injection:
    full (user disclosed personal problem) · light (guarded) · none (neutral/decisive)
  Tier 3 adaptive tactics:
    decisive → close guidance · guarded → back-off · literal-Q → answer-first · else elicitation
  Tier 4 stage assembly:
    STRATEGY_PROMPTS[strategy][stage] + _SHARED_RULES + preference_context + lexical entrainment"]
        Loader["loader.py — Config Hub
@lru_cache on all 9 YAML loaders — read once per process, cleared on restart
QuickMatcher.match_product(): exact → alias → fuzzy (confidence ≥ 0.7 accepted)
  'Cars' and 'cars' share cache entry via _match_product_normalized(@lru_cache)
assign_ab_variant(session_id): MD5(session_id) mod 2 → 'variant_a' or 'variant_b' (50/50)
get_tactic(category, subtype, context): random selection from tactics.yaml
render_template(template, **ctx): {placeholder} substitution"]
